																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">For the whole nation of Israel receive our sacrifice; all are thine; thy own domain keep inviolate.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">Congrega dispersionem nostram, libera eos qui serviunt gentibus, et contemptos et abominatos respice, ut sciant gentes quia tu es Deus noster.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">Gather together our scattered people, deliver them that are slaves to the Gentiles, and look upon them that are despised and abhorred: that the Gentiles may know that thou art our God.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">Bring home the exiles; captives of the heathen conquer or set free; to the despised, the outcast grant redress; let the world know what a God is ours!</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">Afflige opprimentes nos, et contumeliam facientes in superbia.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">Punish them that oppress us, and that treat us injuriously with pride.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">Crush the oppressor, the tyrant that so mishandles us,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Constitue populum tuum in loco sancto tuo, sicut dixit Moyses.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Establish thy people in thy holy place, as Moses hath spoken.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">and to thy own sanctuary, as Moses foretold, thy own people restore!</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">Sacerdotes autem psallebant hymnos usquequo consumptum esset sacrificium.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">And the priests sung hymns till the sacrifice was consumed.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">Then, till the sacrifice was consumed, the priests went on with their singing of hymns;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">Cum autem consumptum esset sacrificium, ex residua aqua Nehemias jussit lapides majores perfundi.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">And when the sacrifice was consumed, Nehemias commanded the water that was left to be poured out upon the great stones.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">and when all was finished, Nehemias would have them drench great stones with the water that was left.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">Quod ut factum est, ex eis flamma accensa est: sed ex lumine quod refulsit ab altari, consumpta est.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">Which being done, there was kindled a flame from them: but it was consumed by the light that shined from the altar.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">Thereupon, a flame broke out from them, but died away when the altar fires blazed up again over yonder. </div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Ut vero manifestata est res, renuntiatum est regi Persarum quod in loco in quo ignem absconderent hi qui translati fuerant sacerdotes, aqua apparuit, de qua Nehemias, et qui cum eo erant, purificaverunt sacrificia.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">And when this matter became public, it was told to the king of Persia, that in the place where the priests that were led away, had hid the fire, there appeared water, with which Nehemias and they that were with him had purified the sacrifices.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">The news travelled, till the Persian king himself was told how water appeared where exiled priests had hidden the fire, how, with this water, Nehemias and his company had bathed the sacrifice.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">Considerans autem rex, et rem diligenter examinans, fecit ei templum, ut probaret quod factum erat:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">And the king considering, and diligently examining the matter, made a temple for it, that he might prove what had happened.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">Good heed he gave to the matter, and after due examination fenced the ground in with a shrine, in witness of what befell there.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">et cum probasset, sacerdotibus donavit multa bona, et alia atque alia munera: et accipiens manu sua, tribuebat eis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">And when he had proved it, he gave the priests many goods, and divers presents, and he took and distributed them to them with his own hand.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">Largesse the priests had, and many were the gifts passed from hand to hand, when the truth of the matter was proved. </div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">Appellavit autem Nehemias hunc locum Nephthar, quod interpretatur Purificatio: vocatur autem apud plures Nephi.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">And Nehemias called this place Nephthar, which is interpreted purification. But many call it Nephi.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">As for the place, Nehemias himself called it Nephthar, which means Purification; but the vulgar call it Nephi.</div></div></td>
								</tr>					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
